data.name: txtReason.Text
data.value: I am the author of the document.

data.name: labelComment.Text
data.value: This is a C# sample for the Microsoft Visual Studio. It uses the 3-Heights(TM) PDF to PDF/A Converter API and shows how to convert a PDF document to PDF/A and optionally apply an invisible digital signature with Time-stamp.

data.name: label7.Text
data.value: If the input file is protected by a user password (password required to open the file), either the user or the owner password must be provided. Otherwise the password can be left blank.

data.name: label13.Text
data.value: Required for digital signature: In order to sign a PDF document, a valid certificate name must be provided. The certificate name corresponds to the value "Issued To" in the Windows certificate store. See also documentation.

data.name: label16.Text
data.value: Defining a Color Space or Output Intent Profile is optional. See chapter "Color Spaces" in the user manual for a detailed description.

data.name: label19.Text
data.value: Optional: The signature reason adds a descriptive text.

data.name: label11.Text
data.value: Optional: The URL of a Time-stamp server. Non-working example URL: http://tsa.domain.com:8080/tsp

data.name: label12.Text
data.value: Configure which conversion errors shall be reported.

data.name: label20.Text
data.value: Allow automatic downgrade of the PDF/A conformance level, e.g. from PDF/A-1a to PDF/A-1b.
